Preventive Measures
- Educate the public about the following:(1,2)
 exercising good hand hygiene to prevent cross-contamination with other foods after handling raw poultry,
 washing cutting boards, counter tops and utensils with soap and water after contact with raw meat,
 cooking meats thoroughly,
 washing hands after contact with farm animals, pets, animal feces, and animal environments, especially where the
animals/pets are ill with diarrhea,
consuming only pasteurized milk, dairy products, and juices,
accessing and drinking safe water supplies, and
testing private water supplies for presence of bacterial contamination, if suspected
- Educate food handlers about:(1,2)
 proper food and equipment handling, preparation, and hygiene, especially in avoiding cross-contamination from raw
meat products, and
 thorough hand washing before and after meal preparation.

